  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Retrospective study to evaluate if fibtem predicts the amount of postoperative bleeding in
      total knee replacement patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      This study retrospectively evaluate patients who underwent total knee replacement
      arthroplasty. Laboratory coagulation parameters, including FIBTEM, before anesthesia
      induction and after admission to the post-anesthetic care unit and amounts of postoperative
      hemorrhage and transfusion were reviewed.

      A correlation coefficient of ρ = 0.3 was calculated from a pilot study. We need at least 84
      subjects with an α value of 0.05 and a power of 0.8.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
